HOW TO INSTALL
=======================

To install KIM on your computer:

Copy the variables.example file to variables.sh
Then update the information inside the script to set the variables as desired. If not done prior to running the installer the file will need to be modified at $HOME/.kim/variables.sh

Then run 

./install.sh

as your user and select the option for installation.


HOW TO UNINSTALL
======================

To uninstall KIM from your computer, run

./uninstall.sh

as root and select the uninstall option.
